Notebook Testing_environment¶

The sixth and final notebook in the Master Thesis of Robert Sietsma. Contains mainly code that is inspired by the other notebooks, but has some tweaks to the readability of the figures or code. Or some testing code that were required in further steps of the Thesis.

In [15]:
for gene in merge['gene'].unique():
    subset = merge[merge['gene'] == gene]
    if subset['binarized_label'].unique().size > 1:
        n_benign = subset[subset['binarized_label'] == 0].shape[0]
        n_malign = subset[subset['binarized_label'] == 1].shape[0]
        n_tot = n_benign + n_malign
        y_true = np.array(subset['binarized_label'])
        y_score = np.array(subset['probabilities'])
        auc = roc_auc_score(y_true=y_true, y_score=y_score)
        output_df = output_df.append(
            pd.DataFrame(
                {
                    'gene':gene,
                    'auc':auc,
                    'n_tot':n_tot,
                    'n_benign':n_benign,
                    'n_malign':n_malign
                }, index=[0]   
            ), ignore_index=False
        )
In [16]:
for column in ['n_tot','n_benign','n_malign']:
    output_df[column] = output_df[column].astype(np.int64)

In [131]:
curr = 'n_tot'
output_df[[curr,'auc']].plot(kind='scatter', x=curr,y='auc')
rho, pval = scipy.stats.spearmanr(output_df[curr], output_df['auc'])
int_outputdf_max = int(output_df[curr].max())
x_axis = np.linspace(0, int_outputdf_max, int_outputdf_max, endpoint=True)
x = np.array(output_df[curr])
y = np.array(output_df['auc'])
slope, intercept, rvalue, pvalue, stderr = scipy.stats.linregress(x,y)
plt.plot(x, intercept + slope * x, "r-", label=f'Fitted line (R\N{SUPERSCRIPT TWO}: {round(rvalue ** 2, 4)})')
plt.plot([],[], " ", label=f'CC: {round(rho, 4)}')
plt.plot([],[], " ", label=f'P-value: {round(pval, 2)}')
plt.title('Number of total variants correlation analysis')
plt.xlabel('Number of variants')
plt.ylabel('Performance (AUC)')
plt.legend(loc='lower right')
plt.show()

x = np.array(output_df['n_benign'])
y = np.array(output_df['auc'])
popt, pcov = scipy.optimize.curve_fit(func, x, y)
popt = np.round(popt, decimals=4)
y_exp = func(x_axis, *popt)
y_pred = func(x, *popt)
y_err = y_pred - y
print(1.0 - np.var(y_err) / np.var(y))
covar = np.sqrt(np.diag(pcov))
plt.plot(x_axis, y_exp, c='black', label=f'Correlation (covariance = {round(covar[0], 4)})')
plt.plot([],[], " ", label=f'CC: {round(rho, 4)}')
plt.plot([],[], " ", label=f'P-value: {round(pval, 2)}')

In [95]:
data = pd.read_csv('./not_saving_directory/auc_analysis_model1.csv', low_memory=False, index_col=0)
with open('umcg_genepanels.json', 'r') as json_file:
    genepanels = json.load(json_file)
logn = []
for key, value in genepanels['Neurogenetica'].items():
    for gene in value:
        if gene not in logn:
            logn.append(gene)

logc = []
for key, value in genepanels['Hart- en vaatziekten'].items():
    for gene in value:
        if gene not in logc:
            logc.append(gene)

aucs_neuro = np.array(data[data['gene'].isin(logn)]['auc'])
aucs_heart = np.array(data[data['gene'].isin(logc)]['auc'])
from scipy import stats
stats.ttest_ind(aucs_neuro, aucs_heart)
